The Vice President of the United States, Kamala Harris, delivered a toast at a state banquet in Jubilee House, Accra, Ghana. She expressed her condolences for the tragedy in Nashville, Tennessee, and mentioned the importance of the Ghanaian President's efforts in connecting the African diaspora to the continent. She highlighted the commitment of President Joe Biden and herself to strengthen the ties between the US and Ghana. She emphasized the interconnected history between the two nations and the shared destiny of Black people around the world. The Vice President praised Ghana's leadership and advocacy on the world stage, referencing its historical significance in inspiring the fight for freedom, justice, and democracy. She expressed optimism for the future and the importance of working together for a better future. The toast was offered to the Ghanaian President.